data.title: Old Fashioned and Wonderful
data.text: This is a diner! The wait staff is exemplary, the food is the best! I ordered double  cheeseburger, 50/50 and a diet Vanilla Coke. The young waiter couldn't have been nicer, the food any better and the restaurant any cleaner. The waiter really seemed to enjoy his job, which is hard to believe in this day and age, and came back several times to make sure we were happy!

data.title: Excellent Steak Burgers
data.text: Windsteads produces the best in the city steak burgers. Freddie's and Culvers are both a distant second

data.title: Classic burger joint
data.text: I have loved Winsteads since I was 5 in 1955.  It has always been a treat.  Now my Grandkids love it  Have a special frozen shake

data.title: Early Saturday for breakfast
data.text: I had my car serviced early on a cold Saturday morning and rather than sit in the dealership waiting room drinking bad coffee and listening to awful television I walked down to Winsteads for breakfast. I was the only customer in the place. I hope they have more business during the week because even though winsteads is nothing special in the food department it is a local treasure unique to KC and I hope they are here forever. I had the traditional eggs, hash browns, bacon and toast. The over easy eggs were perfect with a nice runny yolk that mixed perfectly with the crispy on the outside and steamy On the inside hash browns. The extra crispy bacon was flavorful and the coffee hot and my cup was always full. There are other more trendy places for breakfast in KC, but you can't go wrong with the simplicity of Winsteads.

data.title: Trip down memory lane
data.text: We had a late breakfast here one Saturday morning.  Service was good,  she kept our coffee cups full with a smile.  Restaurant was clean.  Breakfast was good standard American fare.

data.title: Good, but not special
data.text: I ran through for a quick burger and drink, having been told that the burgers were 'to die for.' Everything was tasty, but not special. I will probably eat here again, but I wouldn't go out of my way to go to Winstead's.
